Luclin did not really stand out for me at all, aside from Nexus ports that made your starting race's faction completely irrelevant. I have known people who had never spent a day on the old world anymore. So what if you are DE? Everything is indifferent in this brand new world.<br>
Now comes PoP. I was extremely disappointed with how it was done. Now keep in mind, I love the zones, PoK books, tradeskills, quests for re-using old gear no one bothered with (focus item quests). However my expectatons in term of rpg content were somwhat different.<br>
I thought that different planes would offer a plentora of new quests for people that had the right diet. I imagine that my mage could walk to the tower of Sol Ro and get some sort of recognition for serving his god for so many years. I thought there would be some ways to change / acquire deity:<br>
High Priest of Fennin Ro says &quot;Bring forth the heart of our enemy, and our lord will grant you his blessing&quot;, or something like that. Resulting a quest to kill some difficult mini-boss type mob and get the new deity then.<br>
But alas, no. Not the case. You are basically required to kill whatever god you worship to get anywhere. No way around it. That just goes right through any semblance of reason. And there is little reason for this. I can easily see a way with new raid system where a person could receive a flag, but if he got on an aggro list, the game could make the check against his diet pick (like when you are trying to equip some gear), and TL'ed anyone that matches like Vox/Naggy do to lvl 53 . Not difficult to do at all, and would maintain some sense of believability. Hell, even being KoS to your gods could be explained (you are uninvited guest afterall), but a follower killing their own diet? Not likely. <br>
Oh well, I liked the expansion from slash perspective, but it could have been so much more.<br>
<br>
Oh, almost forgot, I find it funny when druids make those annoying little messages and emotes (&quot;By Power of Karana I smite %T with the hail of snowflakes!&quot;, :emote spreads her fairy wings and prances around). After seeing something like this but spamming 5 lines every damn minute and asking them to turn it off, I get &quot;I am roleplaying...&quot; excuse, and then 2 hrs later I see the same druid quadkiting Dwarven women around BB. Roleplaying, yeah (and they still have something like &quot;Enemy of all that is good, I want you to die in little chunks of %P beef&quot;)<br>
<br>
