<br>
A lot of people are like 25% roleplaying and 75% just playing the game.<br>
<br>
I have to agree that Luclin really killed things plot-wise though.  To me the moon would have all this kind of mystical potential for great plots and encounters and stuff..  And the shissar are kinda cool but also kinda boring.  Often boring to fight as well-- they are no dragons that's for damn sure.  The Deep is cool looking but kinda sucks to fight in.  <br>
<br>
But then..  neo-roman and neo-gothic humans?  Ok I guess...  Their cities are cool as hell to look at and there's some kind of plot I think, but it really didn't work nearly as well as the Giant vs. Dragon thing they had in velious.  <br>
<br>
Then there is the Akheva/Alien race thing which takes way too much work to make sense of.  For the average person that raids and grinds xp the aliens are just totally.. well.. alien.<br>
<br>
PoP seems to be a lot better plot-wise, though. <p><center><br>
